members.name: getKind
members.comment: Returns the kind of this file object.

members.name: isNameCompatible
members.comment: Checks if this file object is compatible with the specified simple name and kind. A simple name is a single identifier (not qualified) as defined in The Java Language Specification, section 6.2.

param: simpleName - a simple name of a class
return: true if this file object is compatible; false otherwise

members.name: getNestingKind
members.comment: Provides a hint about the nesting level of the class represented by this file object. This method may return NestingKind.MEMBER to mean NestingKind.LOCAL or NestingKind.ANONYMOUS. If the nesting level is not known or this file object does not represent a class file this method returns null.

return: the nesting kind, or null if the nesting kind is not known

members.name: getAccessLevel
members.comment: Provides a hint about the access level of the class represented by this file object. If the access level is not known or this file object does not represent a class file this method returns null.

name: javax.tools.JavaFileObject
comment:
File abstraction for tools operating on Java programming language source and class files.

All methods in this interface might throw a SecurityException if a security exception occurs.

Unless explicitly allowed, all methods in this interface might throw a NullPointerException if given a null argument.
